@page "/scheduler/default-functionalities"

@using Syncfusion.Blazor.Schedule
@using Syncfusion.Blazor.Calendars
@using Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs
@*Hidden:Lines*@
@inherits SampleBaseComponent
@*End:Hidden*@

<ActionDescription>
<p>
    This demo showcases the <a href="https://www.syncfusion.com/blazor-components/blazor-scheduler">Blazor Scheduler</a> with its default set of minimal configurations. Here, some of the documentary shows are displayed as events parallel to their relevant telecast timings. The show names are given as event subjects and simply notify the start and end of each event.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Scheduler (event calendar) facilitates almost all calendar features, allowing users to manage their time efficiently. It features easy resource scheduling, appointments rescheduling through editor pop-ups, drag and drop, and resizing actions. It includes a wide variety of view modes with unique configuration options for each view. The available view modes are listed below, with the <code>Week</code> view set as active:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Day</li>
    <li>Week</li>
    <li>Work Week</li>
    <li>Month</li>
    <li>Agenda</li>
    <li>Month Agenda</li>
    <li>Timeline Day</li>
    <li>Timeline Week</li>
    <li>Timeline Work Week</li>
    <li>Timeline Month</li>
    <li>Timeline Year</li>
    <li>Year</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To navigate between views and dates, navigation options are available at the Scheduler header bar, with the active view option highlighted by default. The date range of the active view is also displayed in the header bar. Clicking on it opens a calendar popup for ease of desired date selection.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Touch actions on Mobile mode:</strong>
  </p>
  <table style="width:100%">
    <tr>
      <th style="width:100px"><strong>Action</strong></th>
      <th><strong>Description</strong></th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="vertical-align: top;padding:4px 0">Single Tap</td>
      <td>
        <ol style="padding-left:12px;">
          <li>Single tapping on events opens a popup showing event information</li>
          <li>Single tapping on cells displays a "+" icon on the cell. Tapping on it again opens the new event editor</li>
        </ol>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="vertical-align: top;padding: 4px 0;">Tap hold</td>
      <td>
        <ol style="padding-left:12px;">
          <li>Tap holding on cells opens the new event editor</li>
          <li>Tap holding on events opens a small popup at the top with options to edit or delete, and displays the selected event's subject. Continuing this action by single tapping on other events allows multiple event selection, with the previous popup remaining open showing the count of selected events</li>
          <li>Tap hold the event and move it over the Scheduler to enable drag and drop action</li>
        </ol>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</ActionDescription>


<div class="col-lg-12" style="padding-top:15px">
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <SfDatePicker TValue="DateTime" Placeholder="Current Date" FloatLabelType="FloatLabelType.Always" Width="100%" @bind-Value="@CurrentDate" ShowClearButton="false"></SfDatePicker>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-12 control-section">
    <SfSchedule TValue="ScheduleData.AppointmentData" Width="100%" Height="650px" @bind-SelectedDate="@CurrentDate">
        <ScheduleEventSettings DataSource="@ScheduleDataSource"></ScheduleEventSettings>
        <ScheduleViews>
            <ScheduleView Option="View.Day"></ScheduleView>
            <ScheduleView Option="View.Week"></ScheduleView>
            <ScheduleView Option="View.WorkWeek"></ScheduleView>
            <ScheduleView Option="View.Month"></ScheduleView>
            <ScheduleView Option="View.Agenda"></ScheduleView>
        </ScheduleViews>
    </SfSchedule>
</div>

@code{
    public DateTime CurrentDate { get; set; } = new DateTime(DateTime.Today.Year, 1, 3);
    private List<ScheduleData.AppointmentData> ScheduleDataSource = new ScheduleData().GetScheduleData();
}